


12 recursion interview questions.

https://www.byte-by-byte.com/12-recursion-questions/

gfg
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/recursion-practice-problems-solutions/


Question 1

Write a recursive function that takes a number and returns the sum of all the numbers from zero to that number. (Done)

Question 2

Write a recursive function that takes a number as an input and returns the factorial of that number. (Done)

Question 3

Write a recursive function that takes a number ‘n’ and returns the nth number of the Fibonacci number. (Done)

Question 4

Write a recursive function that takes a list of numbers as an input and returns the product of all the numbers in the list. (Done)

Question 5

Write a function that takes a string and returns if the string is a palindrome. (Done)

Question 6

Write a recursive function that takes a string and reverse the string. (Done)

Question 7

Write a recursive function that takes an array of words and returns an array that contains all the words capitalized. (Done)
Input: ['foo', 'bar', 'world', 'hello'], Output: ['FOO', 'BAR', 'WORLD', 'HELLO']

Question 8

Write a recursive function that takes an array that may contain more arrays in it and returns an array with all values flattened. (...)

Question 9

Write a recursive function that will return the sum of all the positive numbers in a dictionary which may contain more dictionaries nested in it. (...)


Armstrong numbers